name: Palo Alto Networks 7.x
description: The Sumo Logic App for Palo Alto Networks is comprised of four distinct Dashboards, giving your organization several different ways to discover threats, consumption, traffic patterns, and other security-driven issues, providing additional insight for investigations.

panels.name: Top Destination IPs
panels.queryString:
$$PAN TRAFFIC
| parse "*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*" as f1,recvTime,serialNum,type,subtype,f2,genTime,src_ip,dest_ip,natsrc_ip,natdest_ip,ruleName,src_user,dest_user,app,vsys,src_zone,dest_zone,ingress_if,egress_if,logProfile,f3,sessionID,repeatCnt,src_port,dest_port,natsrc_port,natdest_port,flags,protocol,action,bytes,bytes_sent,bytes_recv,packets,start_time,elapsed_time,cat,f4,seqNum,action_flags,src_loc,dest_loc,f5,packets_sent,packets_rcv
| where type="TRAFFIC"
| count as count by dest_ip | sort by -count | limit 10
| lookup latitude,longitude,country_name from geo://default on ip=dest_ip
| count by longitude, latitude,country_name

panels.name: Non-Informational Threats
panels.queryString:
$$PAN THREAT
| parse regex " (?<f1>\S+),(?<receive_time>\d{4}/\d{2}/\d{2} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2}),(?<serial>[^,]+),(?<type>\w+),(?<subtype>\w+),(?<f2>[^,]+),(?<time_generated>[^,]+)," // Standard PAN Header
| parse regex ",THREAT,[^,]+,[^,]+,[^,]+,(?<src>\d+\.\d+\.\d+\.\d+),(?<dst>\d+\.\d+\.\d+\.\d+),(?<natsrc>\d+\.\d+\.\d+\.\d+),(?<natdst>\d+\.\d+\.\d+\.\d+),(?<rule>[^,]+),(?<src_user>[^,]*?),(?<dst_user>[^,]*?),(?<app>[^,]+),(?<vsys>[^,]+),(?<src_zone>[^,]*?),(?<dst_zone>[^,]*?),(?<inbound_if>[^,]*),(?<outbound_if>[^,]*?),(?<logset>[^,]+),(?<f3>[^,]+),(?<sessionid>[^,]+),(?<repeatcnt>\d+),(?<sport>\d+),(?<dport>\d+),(?<natsport>\d+),(?<natdport>[^\,]+),(?<flags>[^,]+),(?<proto>\w+),(?<action>[^,]+),\"(?<misc>.*)\",(?<threatid>(?:\w.*?)?\(\d+\)),(?<cat>[^\,]+),(?<severity>[^\,]+),(?<direction>[^\,]+),(?<seqnum>[^\,]+),(?<action_flags>[^\,]+),(?<src_loc>[^\,]+),(?<dest_loc>[^\,]+),(?<content_type>[^\,]+)"
| where type matches "THREAT" and !(severity matches "informational")
| count as threats

panels.name: Megabytes Sent
panels.queryString:
$$PAN TRAFFIC
| parse "*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*" as f1,recvTime,serialNum,type,subtype,f2,genTime,src_ip,dest_ip,natsrc_ip,natdest_ip,ruleName,src_user,dest_user,app,vsys,src_zone,dest_zone,ingress_if,egress_if,logProfile,f3,sessionID,repeatCnt,src_port,dest_port,natsrc_port,natdest_port,flags,protocol,action,bytes,bytes_sent,bytes_recv,packets,start_time,elapsed_time,cat,f4,seqNum,action_flags,src_loc,dest_loc,f5,packets_sent,packets_rcv
| where type="TRAFFIC"
| sum(bytes_sent) as bytes_sent
| bytes_sent / 1024 / 1024 as mbytes_sent
| fields mbytes_sent

| parse regex ",THREAT,[^,]+,[^,]+,[^,]+,(?<src>\d+\.\d+\.\d+\.\d+),(?<dst>\d+\.\d+\.\d+\.\d+),(?<natsrc>\d+\.\d+\.\d+\.\d+),(?<natdst>\d+\.\d+\.\d+\.\d+),(?<rule>[^,]+),(?<src_user>[^,]*?),(?<dst_user>[^,]*?),(?<app>[^,]+),(?<vsys>[^,]+),(?<src_zone>[^,]*?),(?<dst_zone>[^,]*?),(?<inbound_if>[^,]*),(?<outbound_if>[^,]*?),(?<logset>[^,]+),(?<f3>[^,]+),(?<sessionid>[^,]+),(?<repeatcnt>\d+),(?<sport>\d+),(?<dport>\d+),(?<natsport>\d+),(?<natdport>[^\,]+),(?<flags>[^,]+),(?<proto>\w+),(?<action>[^,]+),\"(?<misc>.*)\",(?<threatid>(?:\w.*?)?\(\d+\)),(?<cat>[^\,]+),(?<severity>[^\,]+),(?<direction>[^\,]+),(?<seqnum>[^\,]+),(?<action_flags>[^\,]+),(?<src_loc>[^\,]+),(?<dest_loc>[^\,]+),(?<content_type>[^\,]+)"

panels.name: Bytes Sent and Received Overtime
panels.queryString:
$$PAN TRAFFIC
| parse "*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*" as f1,recvTime,serialNum,type,subtype,f2,genTime,src_ip,dest_ip,natsrc_ip,natdest_ip,ruleName,src_user,dest_user,app,vsys,src_zone,dest_zone,ingress_if,egress_if,logProfile,f3,sessionID,repeatCnt,src_port,dest_port,natsrc_port,natdest_port,flags,protocol,action,bytes,bytes_sent,bytes_recv,packets,start_time,elapsed_time,cat,f4,seqNum,action_flags,src_loc,dest_loc,f5,packets_sent,packets_rcv
| where type="TRAFFIC"
| timeslice 1m
| sum(bytes_sent) as bytes_sent, sum(bytes_recv) as bytes_recv by _timeslice | sort by -_timeslice

panels.name: Megabytes Received

$$PAN TRAFFIC

panels.name: Top 10 Apps by Bytes Received
panels.queryString:
$$PAN TRAFFIC
| parse "*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*" as f1,recvTime,serialNum,type,subtype,f2,genTime,src_ip,dest_ip,natsrc_ip,natdest_ip,ruleName,src_user,dest_user,app,vsys,src_zone,dest_zone,ingress_if,egress_if,logProfile,f3,sessionID,repeatCnt,src_port,dest_port,natsrc_port,natdest_port,flags,protocol,action,bytes,bytes_sent,bytes_recv,packets,start_time,elapsed_time,cat,f4,seqNum,action_flags,src_loc,dest_loc,f5,packets_sent,packets_rcv
| where type="TRAFFIC"
| sum(bytes_recv) as bytes_recv  by app | sort by -bytes_recv | limit 10

children.name: Requested Apps of Top 10 most active source IPs
children.searchQuery: $$PAN TRAFFIC| parse "*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*,*" as f1,recvTime,serialNum,type,subtype,f2,genTime,src_ip,dest_ip,natsrc_ip,natdest_ip,ruleName,src_user,dest_user,app,vsys,src_zone,dest_zone,ingress_if,egress_if,logProfile,f3,sessionID,repeatCnt,src_port,dest_port,natsrc_port,natdest_port,flags,protocol,action,bytes,bytes_sent,bytes_recv,packets,start_time,elapsed_time,cat,f4,seqNum,action_flags,src_loc,dest_loc,f5,packets_sent,packets_rcv| join( * | count as ipAPPCnt by src_ip,app ) as src_app,( * | count as evtCnt by src_ip | top 10 src_ip by evtCnt) as topIP on topIP.src_ip = src_app.src_ip timewindow 12h | fields src_app_src_ip,src_app_app,src_app_ipAppcnt | sum(src_app_ipappcnt) by src_app_src_ip,src_app_app | transpose row src_app_src_ip column src_app_app

children.name: Targets of Top 10 Attackers
children.searchQuery:
$$PAN THREAT
| parse regex " (?<f1>\S+),(?<receive_time>\d{4}/\d{2}/\d{2} \d{2}:\d{2}:\d{2}),(?<serial>[^,]+),(?<type>\w+),(?<subtype>\w+),(?<f2>[^,]+),(?<time_generated>[^,]+)," // Standard PAN Header
| parse regex ",THREAT,[^,]+,[^,]+,[^,]+,(?<src>\d+\.\d+\.\d+\.\d+),(?<dst>\d+\.\d+\.\d+\.\d+),(?<natsrc>\d+\.\d+\.\d+\.\d+),(?<natdst>\d+\.\d+\.\d+\.\d+),(?<rule>[^,]+),(?<src_user>[^,]*?),(?<dst_user>[^,]*?),(?<app>[^,]+),(?<vsys>[^,]+),(?<src_zone>[^,]*?),(?<dst_zone>[^,]*?),(?<inbound_if>[^,]*),(?<outbound_if>[^,]*?),(?<logset>[^,]+),(?<f3>[^,]+),(?<sessionid>[^,]+),(?<repeatcnt>\d+),(?<sport>\d+),(?<dport>\d+),(?<natsport>\d+),(?<natdport>[^\,]+),(?<flags>[^,]+),(?<proto>\w+),(?<action>[^,]+),\"(?<misc>.*)\",(?<threatid>(?:\w.*?)?\(\d+\)),(?<cat>[^\,]+),(?<severity>[^\,]+),(?<direction>[^\,]+),(?<seqnum>[^\,]+),(?<action_flags>[^\,]+),(?<src_loc>[^\,]+),(?<dest_loc>[^\,]+),(?<content_type>[^\,]+)"
| join( * 
| count as ipAPPCnt by src_ip,dest_ip,src_port,dest_port, threatid ) as threat,( * 
| count as evtCnt by src_ip | top 10 src_ip by evtCnt) as src_ip on threat.src_ip = src_ip.src_ip timewindow 12h| count_distinct(threat_dest_ip) as DistinctTargets by threat_src_ip,threat_dest_port, threat_threatid| sort -DistinctTargets
